      ],
      "task": "Users report that adding a later cache entry can keep an earlier entry alive past its own TTL. Before editing, run the included node repro/per-key-expiry-cache.mjs and use its structured output to identify the first incorrect transition. Fix the root cause so every key expires independently from its most recent set time. A key is expired when now() is greater than or equal to its expiry, zero TTL expires immediately, overwriting one key resets only that key, and reading an expired key must not evict live neighbors. Keep deterministic injected-clock behavior with no sleeps, preserve TypeError validation for clocks, non-empty string keys, and non-negative integer TTL values, preserve the exact direct and public named export surfaces, and keep createExpiringCache as a direct named export. Add focused regressions for per-key insertion times, the exact expiry boundary, zero TTL, overwrite expiry, and isolated eviction. Run the full test suite. Do not commit, install packages, use the network, or create another worktree.",
      "reproduction_contract": {
        "command": "node repro/per-key-expiry-cache.mjs",
        "expected_output": {
          "scenario": "per-key-expiry-cache",
          "observations": [
            { "at": 0, "action": "set", "key": "short", "ttl_ms": 10 },
            { "at": 5, "action": "set", "key": "later", "ttl_ms": 10 },
